        {
          "id": "d1e52e9ca86f_7",
          "href": null,
          "name": "792f",
          "text": "As Winston Churchill once said “first we shape our buildings and then our buildings shape us”; the same holds true for the design of our communities, our patterns of resource use, our education systems, our monetary and economic systems, and our systems of governance. Design goes on designing!",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 294,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 269,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "EM",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "d1e52e9ca86f_8",
          "href": null,
          "name": "c24e",
          "text": "For example, some Japanese city environments are so devoid of trees and plants, that the phobia of having leaves fall on one’s head is now a recognized psychological condition among Japanese teenagers.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "d1e52e9ca86f_9",
          "href": null,
          "name": "bd6e",
          "text": "Design is fundamentally worldview dependent, and the design decisions of previous generations, as well as, the present generation have, at least in part, shaped our worldview and value systems.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 48,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 45,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "EM",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "d1e52e9ca86f_10",
          "href": null,
          "name": "eab2",
          "text": "There is a cyclical relationship between worldview and design, whereby we design solutions, objects, and processes based on our dominant worldviews and value systems, and the world we create around us through our design decisions, in turn, also shapes our worldview. Meta-design consciously creates design solutions or education processes that cause a deeper questioning and a possible shift in worldview or value systems (Wahl, 2006).",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 433,
              "href": "https://www.academia.edu/3991372/Design_for_Human_and_Planetary_Health_-_A_transdisciplinary_approach_to_sustainability_Daniel_Christian_Wahl_WIT_Press_2006",
