        {
          "id": "d1e52e9ca86f_13",
          "href": null,
          "name": "1fbc",
          "text": "The River of Design, sketch by Daniel Wahl exploring the link between worldview and design through the analogy with the hydrological cycle.",
          "metadata": {
            "id": "1*awfX0YtViXtX3KKqamqTEA.jpeg",
            "alt": null
          },
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": "INSET_CENTER",
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 19,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 0,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "EM",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "IMG"
        },
        {
          "id": "d1e52e9ca86f_14",
          "href": null,
          "name": "51a2",
          "text": "Imagine ‘The River of Design’ — way up in the mountains, where rain and snow have fed the ground with the water of life, lies the spring of this river: the level of consciousness (worldview) from which we choose to engage and experience the coming into being of the relationship between self and world begins to shape our worldview and value systems.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 30,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 8,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "EM",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            },
            {
              "end": 301,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 237,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "EM",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "d1e52e9ca86f_15",
          "href": null,
          "name": "ec99",
          "text": "As the stream flows down the mountain what we value shapes our perceived and real needs, and in turn, our intentions and therefore the how, what and why we design. As the little stream turns into a big river, our designs express themselves in the ways we interact with each other and the relationships we form, as well as, through the material objects and physical structures we create. The river of design could now be thought of as three separate but interconnected streams: social design, ecological design, and economic design.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 87,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 38,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "EM",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            },
            {
              "end": 138,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 135,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "EM",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            },
            {
              "end": 144,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 140,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "EM",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            },
            {
              "end": 152,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 149,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "EM",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "d1e52e9ca86f_16",
          "href": null,
          "name": "3d66",
          "text": "As these streams feed the sea of possibilities we live our daily lives in, the structures and process we co-created or adopted (often without questioning) from previous generations, in turn, shape the way we see ourselves, our relationship to the world, and what we value. Water vapour rises from the sea of possibilities and forms clouds that shed their water as they hit the mountains, feeding the springs of the river of design with new ways of seeing and being.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "d1e52e9ca86f_17",
          "href": null,
          "name": "cf6f",
          "text": "Consciousness, worldviews, and intentionality manifest through design. The designs thus created, in turn, shape the way we see the world, what we value, our needs, and thus our intentions.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "d1e52e9ca86f_18",
          "href": null,
          "name": "fc94",
          "text": "Donella at her farm (image)",
          "metadata": {
            "id": "1*UhPNSXFFOGVDI_SKanKuHQ.jpeg",
            "alt": null
          },
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": "OUTSET_LEFT",
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 26,
              "href": "https://climateinteractive.files.wordpress.com/2008/11/barn.jpg",
              "rel": "",
              "start": 20,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "IMG"
        },
        {
          "id": "d1e52e9ca86f_19",
          "href": null,
          "name": "d68a",
          "text": "Donella Meadows famously suggested “the most effective place to intervene in a system is at the paradigm level”. If we can change the way we see the world — the explanatory maps and models we employ, and the value systems we base our intentions and decision-making processes on — we are affecting change at the up-stream end of the river of design.",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
            {
              "end": 15,
              "href": "http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Donella_Meadows",
              "rel": "noopener",
              "start": 0,
              "title": "",
              "anchorType": "LINK",
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "A",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            },
            {
              "end": 347,
              "href": null,
              "rel": null,
              "start": 332,
              "title": null,
              "anchorType": null,
              "linkMetadata": null,
              "type": "EM",
              "name": null,
              "creatorIds": null
            }
          ],
          "type": "P"
        },
        {
          "id": "d1e52e9ca86f_20",
          "href": null,
          "name": "178d",
          "text": "Such subtle culture changes are fundamentally unpredictable and uncontrollable, as they percolate through culture giving rise to new and alternative structures and processes. Influencing the river of design up-stream is design at the worldview and value system level (more).",
          "metadata": null,
          "mixtapeMetadata": null,
          "hasDropCap": null,
          "dropCapImage": null,
          "iframe": null,
          "layout": null,
          "markups": [
